title: Cross country: Lake wins its invitational
text:
Cross country: Lake wins its invitational 
The Clear Lake varsity boysâ€™ cross country team tuned up for the district meet by winning the Clear Lake Invitational this past week at Miramar Park. 
The Falcons were led by Robert Struthers (2nd), Luke Phillips (5th), Javi Villarreal (7th), Hunter Lyde (8th), Alex Bradley (18th) and Joey Bigler (22nd). Advertisement 
Thirty-three teams competed in the meet. 
The District 24-6A meet will be held at 8 a.m., this Thursday at the League City Sportsplex.
